statements: SELECT * FROM machine_learning_models;
SELECT model_name, algorithm_used, accuracy FROM machine_learning_models;
SELECT dataset_name, accuracy FROM machine_learning_models WHERE algorithm_used='Random Forest';
SELECT model_id, model_name FROM machine_learning_models ORDER BY model_id DESC;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_models FROM machine_learning_models;
SELECT * FROM machine_learning_models WHERE model_name = 'Logistic Regression';
SELECT model_name, accuracy FROM machine_learning_models WHERE dataset_name = 'iris' ORDER BY accuracy DESC;
SELECT model_name, algorithm_used FROM machine_learning_models WHERE accuracy > 0.8 AND accuracy < 0.9;
SELECT * FROM machine_learning_models WHERE algorithm_used IN ('Random Forest', 'Decision Tree') ORDER BY model_id ASC;
SELECT dataset_name, COUNT(model_id) as num_models FROM machine_learning_models GROUP BY dataset_name HAVING COUNT(model_id) > 2;
SELECT * FROM model_data;
SELECT id, data FROM model_data WHERE id = 1;
SELECT * FROM model_data ORDER BY label DESC;
SELECT id, data FROM model_data WHERE label = 'example' AND data LIKE '%value%';
SELECT parameter_name, parameter_value FROM model_parameters WHERE parameter_value > 0.5;
SELECT * FROM model_data WHERE id = 1;
SELECT data, label FROM model_data WHERE label = 'category';
SELECT MAX(parameter_value) AS max_value FROM model_parameters;
SELECT MIN(id) AS min_id, AVG(parameter_value) AS avg_value FROM model_parameters;
SELECT parameter_name, SUM(parameter_value) AS total_value FROM model_parameters GROUP BY parameter_name ORDER BY total_value DESC;

SELECT data_feature1, data_feature2 FROM model_data
SELECT id, data_feature3 FROM model_data
SELECT * FROM model_parameters
SELECT parameter_name, parameter_value FROM model_parameters
SELECT * FROM model_data WHERE data_feature1 > 0.5 ORDER BY data_feature2 DESC
SELECT data_feature1, data_feature3 FROM model_data WHERE data_feature2 < 0.3
SELECT model_id, result_value FROM model_results WHERE result_value > 0.8 ORDER BY model_id ASC
SELECT parameter_name, parameter_value FROM model_parameters WHERE parameter_value BETWEEN 0.2 AND 0.5 ORDER BY parameter_name

SELECT model_name, trained_date, training_accuracy FROM Machine_Learning_Models;
SELECT data_name, data_type, data_source FROM Data_Sets ORDER BY data_id DESC;
SELECT model_id, evaluation_date, evaluation_metric, metric_value FROM Model_Performance WHERE model_id = 1;
SELECT prediction_result, prediction_date, model_id FROM Model_Predictions WHERE prediction_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT * FROM Model_Predictions WHERE model_id = 2 AND input_data LIKE '%pattern%';
SELECT * FROM Machine_Learning_Models WHERE trained_date >= '2021-01-01';
SELECT data_name, data_type FROM Data_Sets WHERE data_source = 'Kaggle' AND data_type = 'CSV';
SELECT model_name, training_accuracy FROM Machine_Learning_Models ORDER BY trained_date DESC;
SELECT model_id, evaluation_metric, metric_value FROM Model_Performance WHERE evaluation_metric LIKE '%accuracy%' AND metric_value > 0.8;
SELECT prediction_id, prediction_date, input_data, prediction_result FROM Model_Predictions WHERE prediction_result = 'Success' ORDER BY prediction_date ASC;
SELECT * FROM users;
SELECT user_name, age FROM users WHERE gender='Male';
SELECT product_name, price FROM products ORDER BY price DESC;
SELECT user_name, category FROM users JOIN products ON users.user_id = products.product_id;
SELECT review_text, rating FROM reviews WHERE rating > 3;
SELECT user_name, age FROM users WHERE age > 30 ORDER BY age DESC;
SELECT product_name, price FROM products WHERE category = 'Electronics' ORDER BY price ASC;
SELECT user_name, product_name, purchase_date FROM users JOIN purchases ON users.user_id = purchases.user_id ORDER BY purchase_date DESC;
SELECT user_name, product_name, rating FROM reviews JOIN users ON reviews.user_id = users.user_id ORDER BY rating DESC;
SELECT user_name, product_name, predicted_rating FROM predictions JOIN users ON predictions.user_id = users.user_id WHERE predicted_rating > 4 ORDER BY predicted_rating DESC;
